Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Toss @cauliflower florets{10%oz} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until tender and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Bring @water{1%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil in a small #pot{}. Stir in @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup} and cover. Lower heat and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Remove from heat and keep covered until meal is ready.

Meanwhile, heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a small pan over medium heat. Stir in @chili flakes{1%tsp} (to taste—start with a pinch and add more if you like it spicy), @cumin{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{to taste}. Cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Remove from heat and set aside.

Quarter @Persian cucumber{1} lengthwise, then chop into ½-inch pieces. Pick @dill{1/4%oz} fronds from stems and roughly chop. Zest @lemon{1}, then cut into halves. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz} lengthwise.

In a small #bowl{}, mix together @yogurt{1/2%cup}, ¼ cup cucumber, half the dill, and a squeeze of lemon. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide bulgur between plates. Top with tomatoes, remaining cucumber, and cauliflower. Dollop with tzatziki sauce. Garnish with @pepitas{1%oz}, lemon zest, and remaining dill (to taste), then lightly drizzle with spiced oil.